    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Broome | Betchworth | Surrey</placeName>
                    <date>4 November 1858</date>
                    <salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I wish to be in London on the 25 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> in order that I may attend the meeting of the Royal Society: &amp; this will keep me there until the following morning. We shall be most happy to receive you (&amp; Miss Henslow if she finds it convenient to come to us) on the 23 <hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. But as far as I can see at present, save &amp; except the 18 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi>, 25 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; 30 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> of this month any time will be convenient to us. If I hear nothing further we shall hope for the pleasure of seeing you on the 23 <hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</p>
                  <p>Believe me | always yours truly |B C Brodie</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
    </text>
